#[doc = "Clones a graph\nThis function creates a copy of `originalGraph` and returns it in `phGraphClone.`\nAll parameters are copied into the cloned graph. The original graph may be modified\nafter this call without affecting the clone.\nChild graph nodes in the original graph are recursively copied into the clone.\n\\note: Cloning is not supported for graphs which contain memory allocation nodes,\nmemory free nodes, or conditional nodes.\n\n# Arguments\n\n* `phGraphClone` -  - Returns newly created cloned graph\n* `originalGraph` - - Graph to clone\n\n# Returns\n\n::CUDA_SUCCESS,\n::CUDA_ERROR_INVALID_VALUE,\n::CUDA_ERROR_OUT_OF_MEMORY\n\\note_graph_thread_safety \\notefnerr # See also\n\n> [`::cuGraphCreate,`]\n::cuGraphNodeFindInClone"]
